Package proj

Class StudentCourseListCtrl

java.lang.Object
proj.StudentCourseListCtrl
public class StudentCourseListCtrl
extends java.lang.Object
Represents the control for studentList and courseList combined which holds an ArrayList of Students where each student holds an ArrayList of CourseIndexes.
Since:
2020-11-20
Version:
1.0
Author:
DSAI/1 Group 5

    • checkNewCourseClash

      public boolean checkNewCourseClash​(CourseIndex courseIndex, java.lang.String username)
      Checks if the courseIndex the student wants to register for does not clash with the other registered courseIndexs timeslots The registered CourseIndexes of the student is stored in the CourseIndex ArrayList of the student
      Parameters:
      courseIndex - The CourseIndex object which the student wants to register for
      username - The username of the student registering
      Returns:
      true if the timeslots clashes, else false if the timeslots does not clash

    • checkChangedCourseClash

      public boolean checkChangedCourseClash​(CourseIndex initialIndex, CourseIndex newIndex, java.lang.String username)
      Checks if the courseIndex the student wants to change to does not clash with the other registered Courses timeslot The registered CourseIndexs of the courses registered is stored in the CourseIndex ArrayList of the student
      Parameters:
      initialIndex - The CourseIndex object the student is currently registered for but wants to change
      newIndex - The new CourseIndex object which the student wants to change to
      username - The username of the student who is logged in
      Returns:
      true if the index the student wants to change to clashes with his current timetable, false if it does not.

    • checkIfRegistered

      Parameters:
      username - The username of the student that is logged in.
      courseId - The courseID that the student wants to register for
      Returns:

    • getIndexOfCourse

      public int getIndexOfCourse​(java.lang.String username, java.lang.String courseId)
      Gets indexID of the courseIndex that the student has registered for, which is stored in the CourseIndex ArrayList of the student
      Parameters:
      username - The username of the student that is logged in
      courseId - The courseID of the course we are getting the indexID from
      Returns:
      the indexID of the courseIndex if it exists in the student's CourseIndex ArrayList, and 0 if the course doesn't exist.
